summary:
I am product manager with over 10 years of engineering and entrepreneurship experience.

This wealth of experience has shown me that I'm a valuable team member because:

• I think big, challenges don't scare me.

• I love to drink from the fire hose. Large amounts of new info in a short time-frame? Bring it on.

• I always want to be proud of the work I do, so I put in the extra effort.

• I'm always the calmest person in a stressful situation. 

I love the idea of a new challenge, and meeting people with cool visions. So whether you want to talk about an idea, a design, or a job, I'm all ears.

awards.title: COVID-19 Global Innovation Award
awards.description: The winner of the 2020 CANIE COVID-19 Global Innovation Award is CleanSlate UV. Founded in 2014 out of Queen’s University in Kingston, Ontario, this organization allows staff, patients and visitors to sanitize their personal items such as phones and tablets through the use of effective and easy-to-use UV light products. By harnessing this technology, CleanSlate UV makes it possible to eliminate germs on mobile devices to improve hand hygiene and reduce the risk of hospital acquired infections. Their solution has sanitized two hundred million devices through more than eight hundred units sold around the globe.

awards.title: Young Alumni Excellence Award
awards.description:
The Crescent Young Alumni Excellence Award honours Crescent alumni who have graduated in
the past 15 years and who have already distinguished themselves in their careers, personal
endeavours and community service. These young Men of Character embody Crescent’s core
values of respect, responsibility, honesty and compassion.

awards.title: One to Watch Award
awards.description: Presented annually to a recent alumnus/alumna (fewer than 10 years out) from either an undergraduate or graduate program who are making significant contributions in their field of endeavour, setting an example for future Queen’s alumni to follow.

awards.title: Finalist
awards.description: Out of over 11,000 applicants CleanSlate UV was chosen as one of 11 Finalists, and was awarded one of six $500,000 prizes.

awards.title: Regional Winner (Healthcare)
awards.description: Winners in Healthcare at the 1776 Challenge Cup 2015 Toronto regional competition.

awards.title: Queen’s Innovation Connector Summer Initiative 3rd Place
awards.description:
Limestone Labs came in third place at the 2014 QICSI pitch competition. We were chosen from eight other teams to receive a $20,000 prize which is being used as seed funding to develop our business.

QICSI is the Queen's University innovation and entrepreneurship program run by the Queen's Innovation Connector.

awards.title: Norris Family Robotics and Technology Award
awards.description: This award goes to the graduating student on Crescent's Robotics Team who has demonstrated his commitment over the years to promoting the goals and values of the Robotics program locally, nationally and internationally. This award was generously endowed by Michael and Janet Norris, parents of Andrew Norris '03 and Jonathan Norris '07.

awards.title: Xerox Award for Innovation and Information Technology
awards.description: This award is given to a grade 11 student who has strong interest in innovation and/or information technology, is effective and enthusiastic in the use of technology and leads other students in new approaches to old problems through innovation.

awards.title: Board of Governors Award
awards.description: These prestigious awards are given to two returning Crescent students in each of grades 9, 10, and 11, and to two new members of the graduating class. Recipients combine academic achievement, athletic participation, community service, co-curricular involvement and leadership skills, and are chosen through a rigorous selection process.

Formed in 1897, the Engineering Society of Queen’s University is one of the oldest representative bodies for engineering students in Canada and continues to be a leader in student initiatives. With over 3000 members currently staying on campus, 15,000 active alumni living throughout the world, and an annual budget of $1.9 million, EngSoc oversees some fifty-eight student-run initiatives ranging from design projects to services to fun social events.
